Networking:
You use these when:
Server cannot connect to internet
Website is not reachable
SSH not working
DNS issues
Port/service troubleshooting

1. Command: ip a
    this shows all the network interfaces and ip like private ip, loopback addresses, network interface names
    this is for knowing that server has ip and it can also help us solve connectivity issues

2. Command: ip route
    this shows how server sends traffic to other routes
    this is for knowing that internet routing is set correctly and also help us solve "no internet" issues

3. Command: ss tulpn
    this is to show all services listening on port
    this is for knowing is http, https, ssh are running or no

4. Command: ping google.com
    this sends packets to google to check response time
    this conforms internet is working and detects network failure
    press Ctrl+C to stop

5. Command: nslookup google.com
    this confirms dns is working

6. Command: sudo apt install dnsutils
    this installs dns tools like nslookup, dig

LOGS:
1. AUTHENTICATION LOGS
This to check ssh login attempts, sudo usage, user authentication, password failur, system access attempts
Command: sudo tail -f /var/log/auth.log

2. NGINX ACCESS LOGS
This checks who visited the website, which pages they opened, users IP addresses, browser info
Command: sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log

One-line summary
auth.log → tracks logins & security
nginx access.log → tracks website traffic

3. NGINX ERROR LOGS
Command: sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log
it tells any errors occured in real time
